SECOND REGULAR SESSION
SENATE BILL NO. 1326
103RD GENERA L ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY SENATOR NICOLA.
5081S.01I KRISTINA MARTIN, Secretary
AN ACT
To amend chapter 1, RSMo, by adding thereto one new section relating to daylight saving time.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Missouri, as follows:
1 Section A. Chapter 1, RSMo, is amended by adding thereto
2 one new section, to be known as section 1.355, to read as
3 follows:
1 1.355. 1. There is hereby established the "Daylight
2 Saving as New Standard Time Pact" consisting of this state
3 and any other state desiring to permanently change daylight
4 saving time to a new standard time.
5 2. The state of Missouri hereby exempts all areas of
6 the state from the daylight saving time provisions of 15
7 U.S.C. Section 260a, as amended.
8 3. On the effective date of this section, Missouri
9 will switch clocks to daylight saving time for the last time
10 and daylight saving time will be eliminated. The time
11 formerly known as daylight saving time will become standard
12 time. After this time, Missouri will no longer observe
13 daylight saving time.
14 4. Notwithstanding the provisions of subsections 2 and
15 3 of this section to the contrary:
16 (1) If the federal government enforces the provisions
17 of 15 U.S.C. Section 260a, the state of Missouri and all

SB 1326 2
18 political subdivisions thereof shall observe standard time;
19 or
20 (2) If the federal government adopts daylight saving
21 time as the new standard time, the state of Missouri shall
22 set clocks to conform with the new standard time.
